SIMPLE: metagenesis
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metagenesis
<hw>Met`a*gen"e*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>meta-</ets> + <ets>genesis</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The change of form which one animal species
undergoes in a series of successively produced individuals, extending
from the one developed from the ovum to the final perfected individual.
Hence, metagenesis involves the production of sexual individuals by
nonsexual means, either directly or through intervening sexless
generations. Opposed to <contr>monogenesis</contr>. See <cref>Alternate
generation</cref>, under <er>Generation</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Alternation of sexual and asexual
or gemmiparous generations; -- in distinction from
<contr>heterogamy</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 917 --></p>

<p><ent>Metagenetic</ent>⟦br⟧
